</div> 
<p><strong>Smoldering Shield</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Small Shields" href="/Small+Shields">Small Shield</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The Smoldering Shield&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Shields" href="/Shields">Shield</a> that scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a>. Small Shields&nbsp;usually weigh very little and give the least protection from attacks. They are often used by players who prefer parrying rather than blocking. Its lighter weight also makes it ideal for quick, agile characters with low equipment weight capacity.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Small shield made upon Mt. Gelmir forged from uncooling lava.<br><br>Resists frost with its heat, and can even be used to deal fire damage if wielded as a weapon.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Smoldering Shield</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>From the <strong>Prison Town Church </strong>site of grace, exit the building and turn right, walking west until dropping down onto the rooftop. Immediately turn left, facing south, and safely drop down onto the rocky ground below. Once there, continue downhill to the east, and drop down to a big roof to the southwest. From there, jump to the rocky ground to the northwest, and continue onward to the graveyard. The&nbsp;Smoldering Shield&nbsp;is found here on a corpse. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=4533&amp;lat=-87.964062&amp;lng=61.254524&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=4533&amp;lat=-87.964062&amp;lng=61.254524&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Map link</a>]</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/gjx27iqiG8c?t=2080">Video Location</a></li> 
</ul> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Smoldering Shield Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Shield&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Shield Bash" href="/Shield+Bash" target="">Shield Bash</a></li> 
 <li>This&nbsp;shield cannot be infused with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>&nbsp;nor buffed with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</li> 
 <li>Increases&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Robustness" href="/Robustness" target="">Robustness</a> by 30.</li> 
 <li>Sell value: <img style="width: 18px; height: 18px;" title="item_value_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_value_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px.png" alt="item value icon elden ring wiki guide 18px" width="18" height="18">100</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Smoldering Shield Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement&nbsp;with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (1)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(1)" target="">Smithing Stone [1]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (2)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(2)" target="">Smithing Stone [2]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (3)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(3)" target="">Smithing Stone [3]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (4)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(4)" target="">Smithing Stone [4]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (5)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(5)" target="">Smithing Stone [5]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (6)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(6)" target="">Smithing Stone [6]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (7)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(7)" target="">Smithing Stone [7]</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stone (8)" href="/Smithing+Stone+(8)" target="">Smithing Stone [8]</a>, and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone" href="/Ancient+Dragon+Smithing+Stone">Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone</a>.</p> 
<p>This upgrade can be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
